<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0415 </DOCNO><TEXT>Significant costs are associated with the operation of industrial steamturbines; prominent amongst these are the costs associated with majoroverhauls and indirectly through reduction in internal efficiency duringopertion. Measures to minimize operating costs and also training measures,which are economically significant, can promise success only with closeco-operation between the manufacturer and the operator. (orig.)</TEXT></DOC>